Towards the end of the season I was a little hurt in the minutes and my standing declined, although in the middle of the year I had an excellent period, but they decided to go in other directions.
After I realized the situation there, I realized it was less of a place for me.
Hapoel Jerusalem is the best option for me and that's why I chose it."
In conclusion, what are your goals for the upcoming season?
"There was a lot of talk about what was in the semi-finals last season when I yelled to Ami Biton (the manager of the team at Maccabi Tel Aviv - 19) 'That's what I'm here for,' so that's why I came to Jerusalem - to take titles."
