Saudi Sky Approaches: Israeli Companies Prepare to Strengthen Lines to the East
The consolidated summary for extended flight freedom over Saudi Arabia: The airline is preparing to launch new flights to the Far East at the expense of destinations in Europe
Israel's largest airline plans significant changes ahead of US President Joe Biden's arrival in Israel.
As we have published in Israel Today, it is estimated that Biden will announce permission for El Al and all Israeli airlines to fly over Saudi Arabia to destinations other than the United Arab Emirates.
The significance of the agreement is that El Al will be able to fly shorter routes to the Far East and Australia destinations.
To do this, the company will have to cancel flights to less profitable destinations, in order to evacuate planes in favor of new destinations.
The destinations to which flights will be cancelled starting this November are Warsaw, Toronto and Brussels.
These are three destinations where there is not a small Jewish population, but at this stage they are less profitable to society.
On the other hand, the new destinations looking at El Al are Tokyo, Japan, Hong Kong, Australia and other places in the Far East.
This is how the move will be carried out: The Dreamliner jets flying to Canada will be released in favor of long flights to the east.
The Boeing 737s that fly to Warsaw and Brussels will be transferred for use to flights to destinations such as London and Paris, to which EL AL operates flights using the Dreamliner aircraft.
So basically the company will be able to release large planes to fly to other destinations in the east.
At the same time, El Al expects talks to be held in the coming weeks regarding the possibility that Israeli airlines will be able to return to Turkey, where the company will be able to operate flights using the airline's Boeing 737 aircraft.
How much will you pay for a suitcase at any airline?
Get the detailed guide to baggage prices at various airlines
Who offers 6 for an additional 10 kg, and where does the price never include luggage?
Prices have changed, baggage conditions are no longer the same and many Israelis are surprised when they arrive at the airport and find they need to add high amounts for luggage they thought were included in the price.
How do you know what the airline's baggage conditions are?
That's what we're here for.
Lufthansa Group (Swiss, Austrian and Lufthansa) – The Lite card includes only hand luggage, if you would like to add a suitcase, you will have to do it seven days in advance through the site at a cost of $70 per direction, on the phone it will cost you $80 and at the airport $100.
In a higher class there is a baggage included in the ticket price weighing up to 23 kilograms, and in an economy premium you can also take two suitcases.
American Airlines offers travelers to New York and Miami a 23-pound baggage and a trolley case.
If you want to add a large suitcase weighing 23 kilograms you will pay $100 towards it.
United Airlines offers a suitcase weighing up to 23 kilograms in Economy Class, Premium two suitcases of the same weight and Business two suitcases weighing 32 kilograms.
Trolley can also be added.
The basic ticket price includes a handbag not exceeding 55*20*40 and weighing up to 7 kg.
A suitcase weighing up to 20 kilograms will cost $40 towards a pre-order.
At the airport the price will be $90 per passenger in the direction.
Turkish Airlines offers an 8-kilogram trolley for flights to Turkey and continues with Endologet to follow-up destinations.
Those who continue with Turkish Airlines to destinations outside Turkey are entitled to a large suitcase weighing up to 23 kilograms.
If you would like to add baggage, it is recommended to do so online and in advance.
Virgin Atlantic can be boarded with a trolley or handbag up to 56*36*23.
If you purchase a Light card, a large suitcase will cost $75 in the field.
If you purchase a regular ticket, it will also include a suitcase of up to 23 kg.
Ittihad Airways allows you to board a plane with a hand bag or trolley weighing up to 7 kg and an additional suitcase of up to 23 kg.
Bisherair price does not include your honor.
If you want to order a suitcase weighing up to 40 kilograms, you will pay $40 per direction in advance, when at the airport it will cost you $80.
A trolley weighing up to 8 kilograms would cost $9 a direction.
The Locust Wiz Air Company allows passengers who have purchased a basic ticket to board the plane with only a backpack.
If you want to add baggage beyond that, the price varies depending on the type of ticket you purchase and the destination, and the prices can reach several hundred shekels per suitcase (150-290 per direction), depending on the weight of the suitcase you choose.
EasyJet makes it possible to bring up a small bag of 45*36*20 provided it can fit under the seat.
Beyond that, on the basic card you will have to pay for an extra baggage.
Anyone who orders a seat with more legroom can bring a large bag of sizes of 56*45*25.
The price of an upgrade to a preferred seat that will also buy more baggage varies between flights.
Ryanair's baggage policy is the most complex, starting with a basic personal case that can be entered under the seat for free.
If you would like to add, you can start from 6 per direction provided that your entire luggage does not reach more than 10 kg, and from there the prices jump and can also reach hundreds of shekels per passenger in the direction, depending on the type of baggage you choose and the ticket you purchased.
On the EL AL Lite card you will be entitled to a hand baggage of up to 8 kg.
If you purchase classic tickets you will also be entitled to a large suitcase that will be sent to the belly of the plane.
Ordering an extra suitcase can cost anywhere from $90-150 per direction if you do so at the airport, pre-ordering the price slightly cheaper.
Exempt from isolation for vaccinated and recovering non-red countries, foreign tourists return.
Landers in Israel received notices from the Ministry of Health that they were exempt from the obligation of isolation upon receiving a negative response to the Corona test.
It was only after that that the ministry issued an official announcement that only passengers from orange countries, although also returning from red countries reported receiving the message
In addition: tourists from orange destinations will be able to enter the country as well as the removal of many red destinations from the list.
At the height of an epidemic – the end of isolation for foreign returnees?
The Ministry of Health sent return announcements to Israel this morning that they were exempt from isolation upon receiving a negative response to the coronavirus test they performed after landing in Israel.
It is also used in red states.
Some of the sent messages informed the returnees that they could be released after receiving a negative reply or after 24 hours at the latest, and some received the exemption after receiving the negative answer.
It was only after that that official announcement from the Ministry of Health said that as of midnight, 4.1.2022, vaccinated or recovering, returning from orange countries will perform a PCR test at Ben Gurion Airport and will be quarantined for 24 hours or until a negative result (whichever comes first).
The decision will be anchored in the order of the Director General of the Ministry of Health and will be brought to the approval of the Knesset Health Committee.
The ministry clarified that vaccinated or recovering persons who have already returned to Israel from an orange country and received a negative result from the PCR test they performed at the entrance to Israel, will end the isolation at midnight tonight and are not obligated to perform a second test.
However, passengers from red countries reported that they too received the message.
Those who have not been vaccinated or recuperated and returned from an orange country will enter home isolation for 14 days, with the possibility of shortening isolation upon receiving a negative result in a PCR test performed as of day 7 of landing in Israel (the day of landing is day 1).
The decision to remove most restrictions on the pilots and especially on the vaccinated comes a day before the High Court hearings submitted by the Association of Travel Offices, the Headquarters for Open Skies and the Hotel Association.
In a hearing held tomorrow, the petitioners are expected to demand the removal of all other red states from the list, with the person backing them in his opinion being Professor Itamar Grotto.
Foreigners can also enter.
The Prime Minister and the Ministers of Foreign Affairs, Health, Interior, Tourism and Transportation concluded that as of Sunday 9.1.2022, the entry of vaccinated/recovery foreigners (as defined by the Ministry of Health) from Orange countries will be permitted – subject to filling out an online form in advance, carrying out a PCR or antigen test before boarding, conducting a PCR check at the entrance to Israel and then entering isolation for 24 hours or receiving a negative response on the inspection (the earlier).
Unvaccinated/unrecovery foreigners (as defined by the Ministry of Health) will not be allowed to enter Israel.
Foreigners from red countries, with the exception of those whose entry was approved by the Exceptions Committee, will not be allowed to enter Israel.
The group plan will not be renewed at this time.
What about red states?
The Committee to Classify States in the Ministry of Health recommends that the government be removed from the list of red states and transferred to the list of orange states: South Africa, Hungary, Nigeria, Spain, Portugal, France, Canada.
The remaining countries are currently on the list of red states: the United Arab Emirates, the United States, Ethiopia, the United Kingdom, Tanzania, Mexico, Switzerland and Turkey.
Another possibility being examined by the Ministry of Health is to exempt from isolating the vaccinated returning from red states.
It is currently unclear whether there is a connection between the messages received this morning returning to Israel and the guidelines that may be received by the Ministry of Health on this issue.
The Ministry of Health has yet to receive a response.
The sky is starting to open: The Ministry of Health is changing restrictions on the country's gates
Immunizations returning from orange countries will be charged with 24-hour isolation
The U.S. states, Turkey, the United Kingdom and the United Arab Emirates will be defined as red.
After long weeks in which it was very difficult to find a destination to which to fly without restrictions, and after all returning from abroad were charged with isolation, alongside a ban on tourists entering Israel - yesterday it was decided to change the procedures and significantly ease restrictions on Ben Gurion Airport.
The Ministry of Health has decided to recommend rescinding the three-day solitary confinement obligation for Israelis returning from orange countries.
So far, any inoculated or recovering according to the Ministry of Health definitions that have returned from an orange country – has been charged with solitary confinement for three days, subject to two Corona tests.
Now, the isolation that will have to be entered by the vaccinated and recovering people returning from orange countries is for a maximum of 24 hours, or until the results of the coronavirus tests are obtained that are performed after landing at Ben Gurion Airport (whichever comes first).
Those who are not defined as immune or recovering will nevertheless be required to enter seven days of isolation subject to two Corona tests, or 14 days without the second test, whether returning from an orange country or returning from a red country.
Immunized or recovering returning from a red state must also be fully isolated.
The list of the latest red states recommended by the Ministry of Health, and which still has to pass the approval of the government, includes the US, Turkey, Tanzania, Ethiopia, Mexico, the UK, Switzerland, and the United Arab Emirates.
In all countries, with the exception of Turkey, the average positives that have entered the country in the past two weeks are more than 5% of the total incoming, which automatically puts them on the list of red countries.
The rate of increase among patients from Turkey is rapid, the rate of positive recurrence from which stands at just over 4%, so it was decided to put it on the list of red states as well.
The most prominent countries to be removed from the list of red states: France, Spain, Portugal and Canada.
Meanwhile, as of January 9, tourists who are vaccinated according to the Ministry of Health's requirements will be able to enter Israel without the need for isolation, and similar to the conditions of Israelis returning from an orange country.
In this case as well, the decision is subject to the approval of the government, which will discuss the issue in the coming days.
It is important to note that few cases in which the government does not approve of the Ministry of Health's recommendations in this area.
Tourists against the restrictions.
The Travel Offices Association, the Open Sky Headquarters, and the Hotel Association filed a petition with the High Court of Justice to lift restrictions on the flyers.
The country lifted most of the restrictions yesterday, but left eight significant countries on the list of red states.
In a hearing this morning in Jerusalem, petitioners are expected to demand that the state cancel the list of red states.
Those who support the petitioners' position are Prof. Itamar Grotto, who is expected to be present at the hearing.
Tourism Minister Yoel Razbozov, who has supported relief in recent weeks with regard to the entry of foreign tourists into Israel, said yesterday: "The abolition of isolation for those vaccinated returning from abroad and the return of tourism to those vaccinated is the right and just thing in this period.
I thank my colleagues in government, who understood the plight of the tourism industry and agreed with me that the damage outweighed the benefit.
The vaccine is the best response to the epidemic, and as such, the vaccinated public deserves to conduct a enabling routine alongside the coronavirus."
With an investment of 200 million shekels: the new resort that will open near Arad
The desert is booming: another luxury hotel is expected to open in about three years
Chef restaurants, private pools and 110 rooms are only a small part of what the hotel will offer.
All the details in the article
The 7 MINDS company from Fattal House and the White City Real Estate Company jointly purchased a plot spanning a 20-acre dew in the Judean Desert, in which they will establish a luxurious resort at an investment of about NIS 200 million. The hotel will be built on the same property as the Masada Hotel, which was demolished about a year ago.
The resort won't open for another three years and will have 110 rooms, some of which will have private pools.
The hotel will also have three shared pools, a spa, chef restaurants, a recreation area, a gym and more.
The person in charge of the culinary side of the hotel is Chef Ran Shmueli of Claro Restaurant.
Chef Shmueli will be the one to build the menu that is expected to have a desert concept unique to the resort.
The mayor of Arad, Adv. Nissan Ben Hemo, welcomed the project: "The decision to establish a new and prestigious hotel near Arad gives the official stamp to the amazing miracle that Arad has made in the tourism field in recent years.
I am proud of the choice of the entrepreneurs and am convinced that this will be a joint success since Arad has tremendous tourist potential."
